Despite the MATCH Act’s stringent restrictions on semiconductors in China, we expect the long-term impact on ASML’s DUV business to be relatively manageable. First, ASML has already guided that its exposure to the Chinese market has decreased to approximately 20%, protecting against further downside. Most crucially, strong demand for advanced logic and DRAM capacity in non-Chinese regions globally will effectively offset the impact of restrictions in a single market. Furthermore, the Act is still in its early stages and will not take effect in the short term.
#### Financial Forecast
We maintain our current financial forecasts. In our Base Case, we estimate ASML’s 2027 EPS to be €43.4, corresponding to a 2027 P/E of 28.4x. In our Bull Case, we account for TSMC’s further expansion plans and sustained ~20% YoY growth in China for both 2026 and 2027; under these conditions, 2027 EPS could reach €48.4, corresponding to a P/E of 25.5x. It should be noted that our Bull Case remains conservative regarding Intel Foundry and Samsung Foundry, and ASML’s own capacity remains tight.
